  "prompt": "3 digit no unit digit, ten digit and hundred digit their ratio 3:5:7 if the difference of original number and \u0155eversing the digit is 396 find the no?",
  "response": "Let's denote the three-digit number as \\(ABC\\) where \\(A\\) is the hundred's digit, \\(B\\) is the ten's digit, and \\(C\\) is the unit's digit. According to the given ratio of 3:5:7, we can write:\n\n\\[ A = 7x \\]\n\\[ B = 5x \\]\n\\[ C = 3x \\]\n\nThe original number \\(ABC\\) can be expressed as:\n\n\\[ 100A + 10B + C = 100(7x) + 10(5x) + 3x = 700x + 50x + 3x = 753x \\]\n\nThe reversed number \\(CBA\\) can be expressed as:\n\n\\[ 100C + 10B + A = 100(3x) + 10(5x) + 7x = 300x + 50x + 7x = 357x \\]\n\nAccording to the given difference between the original number and the reversed number:\n\n\\[ 753x - 357x = 396 \\]\n\nSimplify the equation:\n\n\\[ 396x = 396 \\]\n\nSolve for \\(x\\):\n\n\\[ x = 1 \\]\n\nNow substitute \\(x = 1\\) back into \\(A\\), \\(B\\), and \\(C\\):\n\n\\[ A = 7x = 7 \\]\n\\[ B = 5x = 5 \\]\n\\[ C = 3x = 3 \\]\n\nThus, the original number \\(ABC\\) is:\n\n\\[ 753 \\]\n\nSo, the number is 753.",
